title: BRN Email Communications (Board Of Registered Nursing California)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All emails sent or received by Ms. Shannon Johnson, BRN Enforcement Chief, from September 1, 2023, to May 29, 2024, regarding the BRN’s Intervention and Diversion Program. Individual participant names may be redacted. 

All emails sent or received by Ms. Jaspreet Pabla, Program Manager, from September 1, 2023, to May 29, 2024, regarding the BRN’s Intervention and Diversion Program. Individual participant names may be redacted. 

All emails sent or received by Ms. Evon Lenerd Tapps, Assistant Executive Officer, from September 1, 2023, to May 29, 2024, regarding the BRN’s Intervention and Diversion Program. Individual participant names may be redacted. 

All Board of Registered Nursing organization charts as existed between January 1, 2020, and May 29, 2024.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jeffrey Hanson
